President Donald J. Trump and Prime Minister Narendra Modi of India spoke and discussed various issues. They pledged to work together to enhance security and prosperity in the Indo-Pacific region. They also expressed their commitment to supporting Afghanistan's security and stability. The leaders expressed concern about the political crisis in Maldives and emphasized the importance of democratic institutions and rule of law. They discussed the situation in Burma and ways to address the Rohingya refugee crisis. Additionally, they talked about steps to ensure the denuclearization of North Korea. Finally, they agreed to strengthen security and economic cooperation and look forward to the 2+2 ministerial dialogue in April.